She's gonna tell Michael.
And he won't hear the good stuff.

274
00:13:46,764 --> 00:13:48,925
He'll just hear about the beating.

275
00:13:49,033 --> 00:13:52,264
Wait. Maybe we can give her
a "forget-me-now." Here you go, hot dog.

276
00:13:52,370 --> 00:13:54,838
- Take the pill.
- What's a forget-me-now?

277
00:13:54,939 --> 00:13:57,373
They're pills that create
a sort of temporary "forgettiness."

278
00:13:57,475 --> 00:13:59,130
If somebody finds out
how you do a trick, you

279
00:13:59,143 --> 00:14:00,808
give them one, and they
forget the whole thing.

280
00:14:00,912 --> 00:14:02,015
Oh.

281
00:14:02,028 --> 00:14:03,142
It's a mainstay of the
magician's tool kit.

282
00:14:03,247 --> 00:14:05,613
Like how clowns always have
a rag soaked in ether.

283
00:14:05,717 --> 00:14:08,618
Gob, this is flunitrazepam.
It's a roofie.

284
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:11,211
- Those are illegal!
- Shut up, Mom.

285
00:14:11,322 --> 00:14:13,381
Don't make me give you
another one of these.

286
00:14:14,992 --> 00:14:17,961
Lindsay, help me! Three!

287
00:14:21,599 --> 00:14:24,033
<i>Back at the house,
Michael finished his work...</i>

288
00:14:24,135 --> 00:14:26,069
<i>and, now late,
rushed to pick up Rita.</i>

289
00:14:26,170 --> 00:14:30,630
<i>Moments later, Maeby prepared to tell
Steve she wasn't ready for romance.</i>

290
00:14:30,742 --> 00:14:33,176
Well, this sends a mixed message.

291
00:14:33,277 --> 00:14:36,041
<i>Just as Steve showed up
to call things off with his cousin.</i>

292
00:14:36,147 --> 00:14:38,809
- You did all this for me?
- Yes.

293
00:14:38,916 --> 00:14:42,249
Well, I'm gonna go get sexy.

294
00:14:44,956 --> 00:14:47,516
<i>And Michael missed Rita.</i>

295
00:14:49,627 --> 00:14:52,858
Damn it. Strike two.

296
00:14:53,964 --> 00:14:56,593
Take it down. We don't want
anything that says Rita.

297
00:14:56,701 --> 00:14:59,602
<i>Hi. It's Michael.
I will be coming to the party...</i>

298
00:14:59,704 --> 00:15:02,696
<i>because I love you too.</i>

299
00:15:02,807 --> 00:15:05,332
Okay. We need a new banner.

300
00:15:05,443 --> 00:15:08,139
<i>And that's when Michael found Rita.</i>

301
00:15:08,246 --> 00:15:10,146
Rita.

302
00:15:10,248 --> 00:15:12,773
- Why am I on a bus bench, Michael?
- I get it.

303
00:15:12,884 --> 00:15:16,877
I'm sorry. But the rest of the night's
gonna be all about you, I promise.

304
00:15:16,988 --> 00:15:18,888
Great. Great.

305
00:15:18,990 --> 00:15:21,185
I am gonna have to make one quick stop,
maybe you'd just wait in the car.

306
00:15:21,292 --> 00:15:23,783
It's just gonna be
two seconds, I promise.

307
00:15:23,895 --> 00:15:26,728
<i>And so Michael raced up to pay
his quick respects to Buster.</i>

308
00:15:26,831 --> 00:15:29,527
Ah, there he is...
my favorite son.

309
00:15:29,634 --> 00:15:31,932
- Everybody's favorite son!
- Mr. Wonderful!

310
00:15:32,036 --> 00:15:35,369
Well, I had a great time.
I wish I could've stayed longer.

311
00:15:35,473 --> 00:15:38,533
This is a great party, huh?
Tell Buster I stopped by, please.

312
00:15:38,643 --> 00:15:40,634
- I do have to leave.
- Oh, no, no, no.

313
00:15:40,745 --> 00:15:43,805
The party is not for Buster anymore.

314
00:15:43,915 --> 00:15:45,815
- No, Michael. It's for you.
- Me.

315
00:15:45,917 --> 00:15:48,715
Take a look at banner, Michael!

316
00:15:48,820 --> 00:15:52,586
You guys did all of this for me?
"Family love"...

317
00:15:52,690 --> 00:15:55,750
<i>- Michael?
- Everyone froze.</i>

318
00:15:55,860 --> 00:15:59,387
<i>Michael feared he'd been caught
in a lie about his family.</i>

319
00:15:59,497 --> 00:16:01,556
<i>His family feared
they'd been caught...</i>

320
00:16:01,666 --> 00:16:05,466
<i>by a woman they clubbed,
drugged and left on a bench.</i>

321
00:16:05,570 --> 00:16:07,470
<i>It was awkward.</i>

322
00:16:07,572 --> 00:16:10,370
- Who's this?
- Mother! Mother!

323
00:16:10,475 --> 00:16:13,535
This is from the army.
I have to report for duty tomorrow!

324
00:16:13,644 --> 00:16:15,908
It says by accepting this
medal, I was reenlisting.

325
00:16:16,013 --> 00:16:17,913
I didn't hear them say that.

326
00:16:18,015 --> 00:16:20,540
<i>Perhaps if the sergeant had
spoken more slowly, she would have.</i>

327
00:16:20,651 --> 00:16:23,381
In acceptance of this medal, you proudly
waive all rights to private citizenship...

328
00:16:23,488 --> 00:16:26,013
and hereby reenlist in the armed services
of the United States.

329
00:16:26,123 --> 00:16:28,023
If you agree with this,
say thank you.

330
00:16:28,125 --> 00:16:30,491
Thank you.

331
00:16:30,595 --> 00:16:33,758
What am I gonna do?
I can't go back there. I've never been!

332
00:16:33,865 --> 00:16:36,993
- Who are these people?
- This is my family.

333
00:16:37,101 --> 00:16:39,535
No. No.
I don't like these people.

334
00:16:39,637 --> 00:16:42,606
Me. You mean... She means me.
Because I lied...

335
00:16:42,707 --> 00:16:46,609
about having a family, because
I was embarrassed by them.

336
00:16:46,711 --> 00:16:48,611
And I'm ashamed of that.

337
00:16:48,713 --> 00:16:50,613
I have to leave.

338
00:16:53,551 --> 00:16:55,382
Strike three.

339
00:16:55,486 --> 00:16:58,614
You said you didn't have a family?

340
00:16:58,723 --> 00:17:01,954
- Everybody's favorite son.
- Mr. Terrible.

341
00:17:04,495 --> 00:17:06,395
And her?
Too good for us? Huh.

342
00:17:06,497 --> 00:17:08,692
Buster, you should've
finished the job.

343
00:17:08,799 --> 00:17:12,064
- Job? What job?
- Did I say job? I meant Gob.

344
00:17:12,169 --> 00:17:15,502
Buster's the one that hit her.
I just gave her the roofie.

345
00:17:15,606 --> 00:17:17,369
- Roofie?
- Forget-me-now.

346
00:17:17,475 --> 00:17:19,375
You beat and drugged Rita?

347
00:17:22,280 --> 00:17:23,872
- Take this and love us again.
- No, no, no!

348
00:17:23,981 --> 00:17:26,040
- Just take it!
- No, Gob!

349
00:17:26,150 --> 00:17:28,414
Um, I'm leaving too.

350
00:17:30,087 --> 00:17:34,148
Well, no good deed
goes unpunished.

351
00:17:34,258 --> 00:17:36,226
Oh, look, it's not all bad.

352
00:17:36,327 --> 00:17:40,058
I got Buster feeling
better about his... medal.

353
00:17:40,164 --> 00:17:43,224
Not anymore.
I'm getting rid of this thing.

354
00:17:43,334 --> 00:17:46,599
It has caused me nothing
but pride and self-respect!

355
00:17:46,704 --> 00:17:48,831
<i>Buster went to get rid of the medal...</i>

356
00:17:48,940 --> 00:17:50,874
<i>he finally felt he deserved...</i>

357
00:17:50,975 --> 00:17:53,910
<i>but it was exactly when George Sr.
Was making his escape.</i>

358
00:17:54,011 --> 00:17:56,172
Farewell to you all!

359
00:17:59,116 --> 00:18:02,677
<i>But it turns out that hydrogen
is more explosive than helium.</i>

360
00:18:12,363 --> 00:18:15,526
<i>And George Michael came home
to find an unconscious Steve Holt.</i>

361
00:18:15,633 --> 00:18:18,534
- What have you guys been doing?
- I gave him a roofie.

362
00:18:18,636 --> 00:18:20,570
A girl's gotta grow up sometime.

363
00:18:20,671 --> 00:18:23,037
- He's your cousin!
- My cousin?

364
00:18:23,140 --> 00:18:27,474
